Nairobi Governor Johnson Sakaja is on TikTok. His page has more than 211,000 followers after one day. He said it will be fun and light relief. "Hey guys, I am finally on Tiktok. This is my actual page, let me know what to do next on these streets, karibuni," he captioned in one of the videos. In yet another video, he expressed how excited he is to have gained so many followers. "I think I will enjoy this. Thank you for finishing up at the office. Wacha niende home ni-relax. I hope you are not in a noisy bar. Kesho kanisa kama kawa." His fans have also been engaging him in the comment section, with many asking him to respond to their comments.